  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provide creative economy enterprise training in low income areas in periphery of S&#xE3;o Paulo. Pilot project will train 50 agents and to replicate to 100 enterpreneurs.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will promote skills and professional development in creative economy enterprise to generate business and technology development through innovation as a way of raising social development and reducing economic inequalities among young populations living in outlying areas of low-incomes that usually are not included in this agenda. The focus of the pilot in the public sector sector, and the target is to train 50 agents, and to replicate to 100 enterpreneurs in periphery of S&#xE3;o Paulo. It will follow the current policy of decentralize training to impact peripheral areas. Study of the town hall, which is foregrounding the project, is attached.</narrative>
  </description>
